values:
This is almost awkward.  Writing here again, I mean.  I have kept my life's pace for what feels like an eternity without even thinking of livejournal until a few days ago.  You all have been through a lot.  And I have unfortunately missed most of it.  But, things have never been more beautiful and confusing.  I am waiting anxiously for school to start again, and I hope you all are, too.  I have found myself a little more this summer, and I have been blessed to have been given the chances I have.  Finding joy in the oldest friends, this has been a wonderful few months.  For all of you - peace.

Oh, and Danny - Congratulations on the amazing job.  Good luck with that, but don't forget to catch up sometime.

So, the girlfriend gave me a haircut tonight, and believe it or not, I think it looks damn good.  A first time for us both.  Anyoldhoo, for all of you complaining about the cold, I wish it would snow like we lived under the rule of the ice queen in Narnia, and for those of you with snow, bring some home for me, okay?

Peace out, bitches.
Go Colts, Congratulations Bears, and thanks for coming out.  Ha.
Sorry Brittany and Lindsay had to endure that.  We don't think she did it, just weird circumstances for where he was shot.  Umm, I leave tomorrow, so bye.

Look, we all know the moon's not made of green cheese.  But, what if was made outta barbecue spare ribs?  Wouldya eat it then?  I know I would.

Look kids - for anyone who might give a shit, I would love to see all (or at least most of) your ugly faces while I am home for a grand total of about 11 days.  I know most of you don't care, but I would love to see you, and I would love to do something fun with all of you.  Maybe it won't work out, but maybe it can.  

Please be friends with me, I don't know how much longer I'll be around, and neither do you.  Not to be morbid or weird.  I miss you.  No, not you.  Yeah.  You.

I haven't updated in about a year.  Don't have much to say, just wanted to say I have been thinking a lot about the future lately.  It sure is coming on fast.  My Aunt called me about meeting her in Atlanta with her husband before Thanksgiving and going out to get some beers.  Am I that old?  Holidays with the family, and I am EXPECTED to drink?  Wow.  Where did all the time go?  I love life, and Lindsay.  Okay.  Boring as hell post. Sorry.

I wrote this while sitting through my three hours economic geography lecture.  Crap or not, I don't care.  Tell if you want.  Except you, Alex Bad.  I know what you think.

ghost town (not some prize)

And the rain stops
this wasteland feels more like home
these colors unknown
all mankind is at the door

Learn your lessons
its not meant to be over your head
my brittle hands comfort you
still covering this newborn's heart

Within temptation
I am dismayed
hey baby put me up against the wall
I just won't turn on you

Intending on forever
I put the ice against your back
next and now or never
I'm useful, forever I am yours

I'm in transition
I see your face
I'm really changing
I'm really changing...
But, on a scale of 1-10, that was a fucking 12...

Don't forget to blink...  

I am sorry, but has the world gone mad?  Where is the intense humanity that I needed to feel for all the people I know and love?  No, fuck that.  Where are all the people I know and love?  I am not lost in this madness, but I fear the worst for you all.  Every one of you knows the way to my heart, but will you choose to come and claim it?  I hold no hope or doubt, as my head is no longer able to keep pace with my heart.  But, try as I might, this anxiety will best me long before my dream comes true, and long before I could ever say to you the truth I hold inside.  Don't care.  Why should you.  You all think the same of me.  I am spoiled with this ability to walk with my head up.  To show you what I am is not to change you, but to move you to change.  

Bangerang, bitches.  Bangerang.
I thnik the drugsare workig rige=t now.  I don't feel anht0ing.  YAAARARY

Okay, so hernia surgery wasn't that bad.  I woke up and felt like I was on drugs.  It was great.  Then I came home.  Still feeling drugged up and fine.  Then I tried to pee.  I couldn't pee for about five hours, and what little would come out when I tried, felt like a red hot poker being shoved up my urethra and twisted around a bit, just to make sure I was aware of a problem.  But, it's all good now.  I am peeing every few minutes, and still not feeling like I am on drugs.  What a waste of pain medication.  Sorry if this is whiny.  I am just unable to sleep, and really wanting to just get messed up and pass out from the pills they gave me.  Which don't freakin' work!!!

So, yesterday was disheartening, and let me tell you, that is the last thing I need right now.  Some of you may know that I haven't really been around the last few days, and some of you may not have noticed or given two shits.  I don't get to see my girlfriend for three weeks starting on Saturday, which will be the first day I wake up on drugs after my surgery on Friday.  I am not happy or excited about this.  So, if you want to see me acting more stupid than normal, come see me after Friday night.  I will be on the couch for a few days.  

Also, we have yet to hear back from our producer/friend Jeff, and when we went to talk to the other guy yesterday, he wasn't even there, and we had to talk to some half retarded excuse for a sound engineer instead.  Again, I don't think disheartened was the best turn I could've taken.  

But, my Mom called me this morning to wish me a happy 4th of July, and I got to tell her all about how much fun I had at my birthday party, and I guess I just wanted to say thanks to everyone who showed up.  I really appreciate you all so very much.  I wish I could have seen you all gettin' "to'up" at Glyn's the past few nights, but I am seriously obsessed with this girl.  I love you all, and I hope to see you soon.  Peace.

So, first of all, I want to say I had an awesome time last night.  Thank you so much for coming out to see us!  I think that was one of the most fun times I have ever had playing music.  It was a good show, and I really feel bad for the people who came down and couldn't even get on the damn street because of the ridiculous curfew enforcement crap.  What a crock of shit.  Anyway, thank you so much for your effort.  If anyone actually came down and wasn't able to get on the street, let me know.  I am really sorry about that, and again, thanks for trying.  But, it was an awesome night, and I am glad we got to rock out with Gunderson again!  They rock my face.  Matt - You are the number one cowbell player, ever.  Much better that Gene Frenkle.  Don't you ever forget that.  Thanks again guys.  Peace.

Mrs. Botchagalupe comes to visit her son Anthony for dinner. Anthony lives with a female roommate, Maria.  During the course of the meal, Mama can't help but notice how pretty Anthony's roommate is.  

She had long been suspicious of the relationship between the two, and this made her more curious.  

Over the course of the evening, while watching the two interact, she started to wonder if there was more between Anthony and his roommate than meets the eye.

Reading his Mom's thoughts, Anthony volunteered, "I know what you must be thinking, but I assure you, Mama, Maria and I are just roommates."

About a week later, Maria came to Anthony saying, "Ever since your mother came to dinner, I've been unable to find the silver sugar bowl. You don't suppose she took it, do you?"

"Well, I doubt it, but I'll e-mail her, just to be sure."

So he sends his Mom an email:

Dearest Mama,

I'm not saying that you took the sugar bowl from my house, and I'm not saying that you didn't take it, I'm just saying that it has been missing ever since you were here for dinner.

Love,
Anthony

Several days later, Anthony receives an email response from his Mama:

Figlio mio,

I'm not saying that you 'do' sleep with Maria, and I'm not saying that you 'do not' sleep with her. But the fact remains that if she was sleeping in her own bed, she would have found the sugar bowl by now.
Love, Mama

MORAL: Never lie to your Mother


I thought it was funny, but is he trying to tell me something?

So, I had a really great time at the show last night.  I actually was surprised at how good it felt.  I was very excited about the band right now.  I am also very happy that we seem stronger now that we got that shit outta the way.  Rock and roll.

So, it has been a while since I have made a post on this thing.  I haven't had much time to say anything, or much to say, but I just want ya'll to know that no matter how long it has been since I've seen you, it always feels like it's been too long.  I can't wait for this summer.  I think it could make or break me, in more ways than one.  Pray for rock and roll.

What would I look like with tears in my eyes?  Look into my crimson face and watch my body shaking.  With no voice left after screaming the word fuck over and over again until I can taste the blood in my mouth, what will I do tomorrow?  Here's to the night...

So, I was thinking about the album that we're pretty much done recording, and something that keeps coming to mind is who these songs are about.  I am really surprised at myself, but not really surprised at who inspired me.  It is funny, acutally.  But, Julia can rest assured that hers is the only song with her name in the title.

Tonight held an interesting chain of thought for me.  I can't help but think about how absolutely unsatisfiable I am.  I am kind of depressed and angry at myself at the same time.  Now I've gone and done it.

Well, tonight was fun.  I had a great time, we played a good show, and I think that we will be able to record the rest of our songs sooner than we had previously thought.  I don't know for sure, but I think recording our songs made us a more cohesive unit.  We just seemed more together tonight than a lot of other times.  Drew made me start thinking about track listings for our cd, and it is crazy.  I can't even start to think about what order our songs should go in.  I had been thinking about the whole process, and me and Aaron talked about it a little, but I'll be damned if I don't feel like I am doing something that really gives me a sense of accomplishment.  Hearing your own music on a cd, and having it sound good is an incredible thing.  I have never felt better about my situation musically as I do right now.  Rock the fuck out.


My first try at a track listing:
 1. You Need Me
 2. Come Clean
 3. Breakup #2
 4. Julia Moore (You're A Crazy, Mixed-Up, Mormon Girl, Who Doesn't Know She Could Rule The World)
 5. Making Out In The Front Seat
 6. Drop Dead, Gorgeous (The Dropped-D Song)
 7. Smoke
 8. Jane Says
 9. Eyes Like A Wishing Well
10. Help Me, I'm Helpless
11. Spinning
BT. Knickers

I don't know, but I am really tired, so this might be complete nonsense.  Okay, bye now.

Nathan and Brian come into town tomorrow.  Excited.  Worried.  Show has to be good Saturday, or Danny might be disappointed.  Know I am hoping for a great show, just because of you, Danny.  Love.  Love. Love. Love. Crazy. Love.  Yeah.

But, I thought it would be funny to see what people thought about talking about their most awkward naked experience/s.  I will definitely tell mine, but only after some other people have told theirs.  I am just so inspired by Julia's humility, by the way.  I touched her hooters.  On accident.  Like two or three times.  Yeah.

And my boobs are amazing, too.

Sam --

'How will you be defined in the dictionary?' at QuizGalaxy.com

Is there ever a more alone than when you can't be with anyone but yourself, because you are too much heartache to anyone you are with, but want so badly to be with anyone but yourself?  Is there?  It feels like there is a silent film running in my head, but the soundtrack player is drunk and unstable.  Nothing is in sync, and nothing makes any damned sense.  But, things are rushing by without a sound to help me recognize their urgency.  What to do, what to do...  Kill the piano player.  I can't handle being deaf to the music of my own life.  My life's rhythm is enough to make me crazy, but without the sounds of insanity constantly bombarding me, I would feel as though I was floating listlessly through a sea of angry words in my mind.  I can't handle the only noise being my hateful sense of self.  

So, basically, I need to do something with my life.  And soon.  Any suggestions???

So, I really love to break people's hearts.  In other news, I made a girl that I was interviewing for an R.A. job cry.  In the interview.  With my boss watching me.  It was grand.  I couldn't believe my eyes when her tears started falling.  I wanted to laugh at her, tell her to buck the fuck up, and get over her foolish emotion.  Then I realized my heart is gone.  I am a bastard of almost epic proportion.  I really have pretty much no patience for people getting emotional on me any more.  I mean, if we are friends, I am more than willing to listen to what is bothering you, and I am certainly willing to help you out, but the second you start crying about something that seems dumb to me, I want to just laugh in your fucking face and tell you to quit being so pathetic.  I am seriously pondering what stole the last slivers of my heart.

I got to talk to my brother the other night, and I am so pumped about going to the Virgin Islands for spring break this year.  Drew is coming with me, so it is going to be fucking crazy, and I really just can't fucking wait.  I have said the fuck word a lot in this post.  Maybe it is all part of me turning over this new heartless leaf.  Anyway, I talked to my brother, and he has some awesome shit planned for us.  He wants to teach me to surf, or at least get me out on a board while I am down there, snorkeling, scuba diving, drinking, cliff diving, sailing, drinking, and just a shit ton of great stuff!  I can not wait.  Oh yeah, and Tip Your Waitress is going to Florida the end of February to play a show at Embry-Riddle.  For a fucking chili cook-off.  That is fucking crazy.  I am so pumped about the band right now.  Jordan, your Dad hasn't gotten back to me yet.  I am kinda deflated about it right now.  Any shit, Danny is coming soon, and he is missing two of our shows by like a day a piece, so he sucks, but it'll be fun anyway.  Two 'Hawks are better than one.  Peace out, ya'll.  I gotta get up in 4 1/2 hours so, good night.

If you have ever had a song written about you, and I was the one writing it, it was because of an intense passion I was feeling at the time.  I either loved you or despised you.  So, know that those feelings are pretty much the only ones to inspire me.

So I wrote a song about someone today, and the first verse includes the word 'fuck' about seven times.  Which feeling do you think that song was inspired by?  I will give you two guesses...

I am going crazy. Steppin' Out.  Actin' A Fool.  Gettin' Crunk.  Fishing Without A License.  Hunting Deer During Flu Season.  Licking The Tootsie Pop.  Having A Coke And A Smile.  Breaking Bread.  Lookin' Supa-Fly.  Eating From The Tree Of Wesley Snipes.  Challenging Chuck Norris To An After Dinner Mints Selection Contest.  Climbing To The Top Of Andes Mints.  Taking Heart In Surgery.  Sleeping With The Lion King.  Having Trouble Breathing Through This Plastic Bag.  Still Waiting For Chuck Norris To Call Me Back.  Living In The Moment, But Not Right Now.  Knowing Everything There Is To Know About Hot, Salty Nuts.  Charged Myself With Murder In The First.  And Third.  Questing For Gold, And Booty.  Waiting For An Angelsfood cake.  Liking The Pain.  Dreaming Of Your Mom.  


Look, I don't know.  But, I like it.  It feels...

It is a-mazing what a phone call from a semi-stranger at midnight will do for your spirits.  It was the second longest phone conversation I have ever had.  With a semi-stranger.  How awesome.  Then I worked the desk from 4:30 to 8:00 am.  That, my friends, was not so awesome.  But, I am definitely going to dominate some sleep time right now.  Peace.

Hey, if you have a bunch of pictures from the break, and you want to e-mail them to me (Danny, I would like to make that one shot that you said you liked my facebook picture) I would love you forever.  My e-mail address is sward4@utk.edu.  I would also like to get any and all videos of me being shot at.  Thanks for a kickass break, everybody.

Bt the time most of you read this, I will either be on my way back to Knoxville, or already there.  I just want you all to know that you made this break great, and everyone who came out for new years, I really just hope to God you really had as much fun as I did, because I am still smiling about it.  I love you all.  I will not see you for a while, but I hope when I do, it will be like I never left.  Peace.

So, as it turns out, I think that I have almost no voice left, and I am so majorly excited about being a huge disappointment to everyone who comes to see us.  I hate my body.  I will just go ahead and say I am sorry for my voice, but we are still going to rock the absolute fuck out of whoever comes to see us!!!

So, Alex, thank you very kindly for your southern hospitality.  I truly do appreciate it.  Everyone who wasn't there, that sucks.  For everyone who was there, awesome.  Seriously, I had a great fucking time, and I am glad that you guys helped me get there!!!  

In other news, you need to come to Lauren's ranch for new years, because we are going to rock the fuck out, and if you're not there, you'll never know just how awesome it was...

For real though folks, we want as many people there as possible, so come on down and join the festivities.  As far as I know right now, it is b.y.o.b. and the more the merrier.  Peace.

Last night was fun, and today was too.  So soft...  

Tomorrow is Christmas... no wait... It is Christmas!!!  

Merry Christmas everyone!!!

So, hopefully I will be home this saturday night, but I will probably not be home until early Sunday morning.  So, anyone who is going to be awake, let me know, because I will come and bother you.  I really don't plan on sleeping unless I just pass out from exhaustion.  So, let me know where you are, and when I can see you, so I can come and see you.  That is all.

This looked like a lot of fun, so i thought i would share.
Do it for me.  You know I would do it for you.

I have had so much inspiration in the last few days it has been overwhelming, but I have let my apathy for life in general ruin any chances of remembering any of it.  I have seriously been too lazy to get up and get a pen/piece of paper that my important thoughts have just been thoughts, and now will never be the words they could have been.  I hate that, but boy do I love taffy...
Sorry, but I don't have anything else to tell you.

So, I am going to buy a new amp tomorrow, hopefully, and that means I will officially become the best guitar player in the world some day.  Anyhoo, I can't wait to get home for Christmas break.  I was just thinking about, and I don't think I am going to sleep for like two weeks straight.  I just have so much that I want to do, so many people to see.  Way to important to let sleep get in the way.  If you are interested in hanging out and finding something rediculous to do, let me know.  I am looking for hilarity.  You know how I roll.  Peace.

I am going to Florida for Thanksgiving, so that is good.  What is not good is my Grandpa's health.  He just had his second major heart attack and is in the hospital.  I hope that he is alright so I can hear some more awesome stories during the break.  You guys know what I'm talking about.
So, I gave in, but you took away from it nothing that I wanted.  I guess all I can say is I was born to break your heart.

If you are reading this, leave one memory of you and me together! It doesn't matter if I know you a little or a lot, anything you remember! Next, post this in your blog and see how many people leave a memory about you.

I am the single-most difficult person to please in the entire world.  I have decided it, and there will be no argument.  I will explain why I am more difficult than you, but it will only frustrate you.

I feel like I can go nowhere but up from here.

I want to write a song that everyone in the entire world will hear and like, if only a little bit.

I don't like your subconscious; or at least what it has been telling you.

I want to run through the hills that have forgotten their worth,

I want to hold out for something just a little bit better.

I want to pull out right before it all comes crashing down.

I want so much so bad.

I want you one more time, and then again, and again, and again, and again.

I need you on my side, so please don't ever turn your back on that need.
